{
  "stem": "10181.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then I-- and I found out, though, in-- in our barracks also, a couple of women, you know, got-- I know one woman got-- all the bullets must have gone-- must have gone through her.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then she was, you know, killed, and others were, too.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The other thing I remember in those days, something very interesting.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Like I told you, it was an-- supposedly it was an exchange camp at the beginning.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And these-- some of these Jews with a Palestine-- brought a certificate to go to Palestine were called.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And it was in June of 1944.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were called, supposedly to be exchanged, to-- to send-- be sent to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they were, by the way. 222 of them were called and put on a train.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And this I found, of course, years later-- made their way to-- to-- by train all the way across Europe through Turkey to Syria and made it to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And this was the only [? transfer. ?] And everybody thought, OK, this is the beginning.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Maybe we can get out of this hell-hole and go somewhere, maybe to Switzerland, whatever.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But this was the only exchange to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Then later on, there was-- by the way, these 222 Jews were exchanged for German Templers who were living in Palestine from-- from long before the war and had been interned by the British.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And for some reason, 1944, the German government wanted them back.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I don't know why.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "You know, that's unimportant anyway.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So that's how they managed to-- to leave Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Then there was supposed to be an exchange through Switzerland, and some people were called for that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We weren't, but some people were called for that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "A-- I don't know how many, a few, and they were put on the train.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
